<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Virginia Historical Society, Richmond ]">ViHi</span>: Dinwiddie Papers.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>An Act for raising the sum of forty thousand pounds, for the protection of his majestys subjects on the frontiers of this colony (6 <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Waller Hening, ed. &lt;i&gt;The Statutes at Large; Being a Collection of All the Laws of Virginia, from the First Session of the Legislature, in the Year 1619&lt;/i&gt;. 13 vols. 181923. Reprint. Charlottesville, Va., 1969. ]">Hening</span> 52130).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Dinwiddie had certainly not commissioned all 16 captains by 14 Aug., but he may have done so by 1 Sept., before GW assumed command. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0001" class="document">GWs Appointment as Colonel of the Virginia Regiment, 14 Aug. 1755</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0005" class="document">GWs General Instructions, 13 Sept.</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0006" class="document">his Memorandum, 3 Sept.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0034" class="document">his Orders at Fort Cumberland of 17</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0038" class="document">18 Sept. 1755</a> for the early steps that he took to complete the regiment and to maintain the small garrison at Fort Cumberland.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>GW initially ordered Maj. Andrew Lewis (6 Sept.) to be receiving officer at Fredericksburg and Lt. Col. Adam Stephen (11 Sept.) to be the same at Alexandria, but the pressure of events soon altered these arrangements. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0081" class="document">GW to Andrew Lewis,</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0082" class="document">to Thomas Waggener, both 8 Oct. 1755</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>Lt. Col. Adam Stephen made his first return of the Virginia Regiment at <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0045" class="document">Fort Cumberland to GW on 18 Sept. 1755</a>, and Capt. Peter Hogs first weekly return of the 1st company, at Fort Dinwiddie, is dated 29 Sept. 1755.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0001-0003-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>The records of the committee appointed to supervise military expenditures under the terms of the act for raising 40,000 (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-01-02-0180&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-01-02-0180-fn-0001#GEWN-02-01-02-0180-fn-0001" class="document">Philip Ludwell to GW, 8 Aug. 1755, n.1</a>) have not been found, but GW was provided with a copy of the committees resolutions of 811 Nov. 1755, which included a resolution that began resolved That the sum of 10,000 be lodged in the hands of Colonel George Washington as a Military Chest and went on to indicate for what the money was to be spent (<a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0166" class="document">Memorandum from Committee to Supervise Military Expenditures to GW, 811 Nov. 1755</a>).</p>

</div>
